5:["$","div",null,{"className":"flex min-h-screen flex-col","children":[["$","$Le",null,{}],["$","main",null,{"className":"flex-1","children":["$","article",null,{"className":"container max-w-4xl py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"text-center space-y-4","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-headline text-4xl font-bold tracking-tighter sm:text-5xl","children":"October 2026 Market Report: Why Oakville Remains an Island of Opportunity for Sellers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground","children":"October 28, 2025"}]]}],["$","$Lf",null,{"className":"my-8"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none dark:prose-invert","children":[["$","p","p-0",{"children":"As the leaves turn and the air crisps, the real estate conversation across the Greater Toronto Area (GTA) is shifting. We are seeing a return to more balanced conditions in many pockets, a natural cooling after years of frenetic activity. However, a closer look at the data reveals a distinct and important trend for local homeowners: Oakville's market is bucking the regional trend, presenting a unique and continued window of opportunity for sellers."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"The Broader GTA Context: A Shift Towards Balance"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":["According to the latest market watch from the ",["$","a","a-0",{"href":"https://trreb.ca/","children":"Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB)"}],", the broader GTA market is experiencing a stabilization. The average days on market has seen a slight uptick, rising to 24 days from the 19-day average we saw in the spring. This indicates that buyers are taking a bit more time to make decisions."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":"Furthermore, active listings across the region have increased by approximately 12% year-over-year, providing buyers with more choice and slightly dampening the intense bidding war mentality that defined previous seasons. While prices remain strong, the rate of appreciation has moderated, signaling a healthier, more sustainable market across the board."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"The Oakville Advantage: A Market Apart"}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":"Oakville, however, tells a significantly different story. My analysis of local market data shows that inventory for detached homes, particularly in highly sought-after neighbourhoods like Southeast Oakville, Old Oakville, and Bronte, remains critically low. We are currently sitting at less than 1.5 months of supply in the luxury segment, which is unparalleled in the current regional context."}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":"This persistent supply-demand imbalance means that well-priced, well-presented homes in Oakville are still commanding significant attention. While the \"frenzy\" may have subsided, the demand for quality executive homes is unabated. We are still seeing many properties, especially those that are move-in ready, receive multiple strong offers and sell over asking price, provided the listing strategy is executed flawlessly. The average sale price in Oakville has demonstrated remarkable resilience, outperforming the regional average."}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-2",{"children":"Why Oakville Continues to Outperform"}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":"The reasons for this disparity are rooted in the enduring fundamentals of our community. Oakville's lifestyle—characterized by top-tier private and public schools, expansive waterfront parks, charming downtown districts, and easy access to the city—continues to be a powerful draw for affluent families and executives."}],"\n","$L10","\n","$L11","\n","$L12","\n","$L13","\n","$L14"]}],"$L15","$L16"]}]}],"$L17","$L18"]}]
